Types			Keywords

-Boolean:			Bool
-Character:			Char
-integer:			int
-floating point:	float
-double f. point:	double
-valueless:			void

type modifiers:

-signed, unsigned, short, long.

The operator sizeof() shows the size of data types in bytes.
Example:
	cout << "size of int: " << sizeof(int) << endl;
	cout << "size of double: " << sizeof(double) << endl;

To create a new name for an existing type, use typedef.
Example:
	typedef int value;

	Now value is another name for int.
	value number1;